Package: V8
Type: Package
Title: Embedded JavaScript Engine for R
Version: 2.1
Authors@R: person("Jeroen", "Ooms", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "jeroen@berkeley.edu",
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-4035-0289"))
Description: An R interface to Google's open source JavaScript engine. This 
    package can now be compiled either with V8 version 6 (LTS) from nodejs
    or with the legacy 3.14/3.15 version of V8.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/jeroen/v8 (devel)
  https://developers.google.com/v8/intro (upstream)
BugReports: https://github.com/jeroen/v8/issues
SystemRequirements: V8 version 6 or 7 is recommended, but 3.14 (legacy) is 
    still supported as well. On Debian / Ubuntu you need either libv8-dev or 
    libnode-dev, on Fedora use v8-devel.
NeedsCompilation: yes
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Imports:
    Rcpp (>= 0.12.12),
    jsonlite (>= 1.0),
    curl (>= 1.0),
    utils
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Suggests:
    testthat,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
Language: en-US
